On the receiver machine (10.6.10.143):

nc -u -l 6666
On the test machine (Dell R640):

# Find the right interface
ip route get 10.6.10.143

# Load netconsole (replace eno1 with whatever the above command shows)
modprobe netconsole netconsole=@/eno1,6666@10.6.10.143/

# Verify it's working:
echo "netconsole test" > /dev/kmsg

You should see "netconsole test" appear on the receiver. If it does, you're
capturing kernel messages. Trigger the BMC reset and the pr_crit messages will
appear on the receiver before the system goes down.
